#### 3. Distribution & Attribution
- Displaying, embedding, or referencing content in websites, videos, papers, apps, or social media;
- Sharing the URL, describing content verbally, or directing others to this repository;
- Submitting content to AI datasets, stock libraries, search engines, or public archives.

#### 4. Legal Defenses
- Claiming “fair use,” implied license, or public domain status;
- Arguing that public visibility waives copyright protection;
- Attempting to assert rights via open-source license compatibility or OSI standards.

